{"id":35,"date":"2021-10-07T01:02:21","date_gmt":"2021-10-07T01:02:21","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/cagbcprod.wpengine.com\/?page_id=35"},"modified":"2023-02-13T07:54:41","modified_gmt":"2023-02-13T12:54:41","slug":"green-building-benefits","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/why-green-building\/green-building-benefits\/","title":{"rendered":"Green building benefits"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"padding-top:0px\">\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"better-buildings-are-possible\">Better buildings are possible<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Green buildings are just better, and that&#8217;s a fact. Research shows that green buildings are healthier for people and better for the environment. As building practices evolve, the ways that green buildings benefit people and communities grow. Today, green buildings reduce carbon emissions, energy use, and water consumption, making them a smart long-term investment. Zero-carbon buildings and retrofits are also crucial to Canada reaching its climate goals and will require more green building jobs to maximize potential reductions in building-related carbon emissions. &nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull is-light\" style=\"min-height:326px\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim-0 has-background-dim\"><\/span><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"2560\" height=\"850\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-2003\" alt=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850.jpg\" data-object-fit=\"cover\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850-300x100.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850-1024x340.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850-768x255.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850-1536x510.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/03\/gbb_fullwidth_1_2560x850-2048x680.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-cover-is-layout-flow\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\"><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\">\n<h3 class=\"has-tree-green-color has-text-color wp-block-heading\" id=\"green-building-benefits-include\"><strong>Green building benefits include:<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-top spacing-top-6\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"450\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/1_gbb_icon_health.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1171 size-medium\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/1_gbb_icon_health.png 450w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/1_gbb_icon_health-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/1_gbb_icon_health-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\" \/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<h4 class=\"has-tree-green-color has-text-color has-h-8-font-size wp-block-heading\" id=\"human-health\">Human health<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Green buildings offer occupants better air quality with lower concentrations of CO2 and volatile organic compounds (VOCs). With higher ventilation rates, green building occupants breathe better air, and enjoy higher productivity and better learning outcomes. Since studies show people spend 90% of their time indoors, air quality is critical to better health. People living and working in green buildings actually experience fewer sick days and lower asthma rates. They also sleep better thanks to better access to outdoor views and daylight. And who doesn&#8217;t want a better night&#8217;s sleep?&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-center spacing-top-6 is-style-default\" style=\"grid-template-columns:20% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img decoding=\"async\"  src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/cagbc_didyouknow_box.svg\" alt=\"Did You Know?\" class=\"wp-image-1358 size-full\"\/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-grey-color has-text-color has-h-4-font-size\">Workers in green, well-ventilated offices record a 101% increase in cognitive scores.&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/syracusecoe.syr.edu\/the-impact-of-green-buildings-on-cognitive-function\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">(Syracuse University, 2015)<\/a><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-top spacing-top-8\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"451\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/2_gbb_icon_enviro.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1172 size-medium\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/2_gbb_icon_enviro.png 451w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/2_gbb_icon_enviro-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/2_gbb_icon_enviro-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px\" \/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<h4 class=\"has-tree-green-color has-text-color has-h-8-font-size wp-block-heading\" id=\"environmental\">Environmental&nbsp;<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Green buildings use less water, energy, and natural resources. They also decrease impacts on the environment. Zero-carbon buildings reduce harmful emissions by avoiding <strong>embodied carbon <\/strong>from materials and building processes and <strong>operational carbon<\/strong> emitted by running the building&#8217;s mechanical systems. Green building standards exist to help building owners and operators pursue their sustainability goals and verify that their decisions are achieving the building&#8217;s environmental and energy-savings goals. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-center spacing-top-6\" style=\"grid-template-columns:20% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img decoding=\"async\"  src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/cagbc_didyouknow_box.svg\" alt=\"Did You Know?\" class=\"wp-image-1358 size-full\"\/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-grey-color has-text-color has-h-4-font-size\">LEED-certified buildings consume 25% less energy and 11% less water than traditional buildings. (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.usgbc.org\/press\/benefits-of-green-building\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">USGBC<\/a>)<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-top spacing-top-8\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"451\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/3_gbb_icon_econ.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1173 size-medium\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/3_gbb_icon_econ.png 451w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/3_gbb_icon_econ-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/3_gbb_icon_econ-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px\" \/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<h4 class=\"has-tree-green-color has-text-color has-h-8-font-size wp-block-heading\" id=\"economic\">Economic<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Green buildings make good business sense. While they may cost slightly more to construct, they are more efficient to operate, which saves money in the long-term. Commercial owners find green buildings demand premium rents and maintain better occupancy rates. Tenants also benefit from lower utility costs that make green buildings more affordable to live in.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As Canada works toward its climate targets, demand for green buildings will grow, creating new jobs. Already, green building jobs outnumber Canada&#8217;s forestry, oil and gas extraction, and mining sectors combined. With investment in green building and progressive policies, green building could account for 1.5 million direct jobs and $150 billion in GDP by 2030.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-center spacing-top-6\" style=\"grid-template-columns:20% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img decoding=\"async\"  src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/cagbc_didyouknow_box.svg\" alt=\"Did You Know?\" class=\"wp-image-1358 size-full\"\/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-grey-color has-text-color has-h-4-font-size\">Over 460,000 people worked in the green building sector in 2018, a 55% increase over 2014. &nbsp;(<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/news-resources\/research-and-reports\/canadas-green-building-engine\/\">CAGBC<\/a>)<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-top spacing-top-8\" style=\"grid-template-columns:15% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"451\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/4_gbb_icon_social.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1174 size-medium\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/4_gbb_icon_social.png 451w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/4_gbb_icon_social-300x300.png 300w, https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/4_gbb_icon_social-150x150.png 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 451px) 100vw, 451px\" \/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<h4 class=\"has-tree-green-color has-text-color has-h-8-font-size wp-block-heading\" id=\"social\">Social<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Green buildings can play a role in shaping more equitable communities. Everyone benefits when community members have access to healthy, affordable housing or when communities are climate-resilient and can withstand extreme weather events. Since climate-related impacts tend to impact vulnerable communities the most, it&#8217;s important that green building be part of Canada&#8217;s approach to social justice.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A social justice lens should also be applied to new green building jobs. As the shift to low-carbon buildings and retrofits increases, growing the workforce to meet demand should include strategies to prioritize underrepresented groups.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide is-stacked-on-mobile is-vertically-aligned-center spacing-top-6\" style=\"grid-template-columns:20% auto\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img decoding=\"async\"  src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/02\/cagbc_didyouknow_box.svg\" alt=\"Did You Know?\" class=\"wp-image-1358 size-full\"\/><\/figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\">\n<p class=\"has-medium-grey-color has-text-color has-h-4-font-size\">With investment in green building and proactive policies, green building jobs could number 1.5 million by 2030. (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/news-resources\/research-and-reports\/canadas-green-building-engine\/\">CAGBC<\/a>)<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n<\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover alignfull is-light is-style-banner-ads\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-ocean-blue-background-color has-background-dim-100 has-background-dim\"><\/span><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-607\" alt=\"\" src=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/11\/banner-LEED-hours-scaled.webp\" style=\"object-position:72% 18%\" data-object-fit=\"cover\" data-object-position=\"72% 18%\"\/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container is-layout-flow wp-block-cover-is-layout-flow\">\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-cloud-white-color has-text-color has-h-9-font-size\">LEED covers 9 factors impacting<br> environmental and human health.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-buttons is-content-justification-center is-layout-flex wp-container-core-buttons-layout-1 wp-block-buttons-is-layout-flex\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-cloud-white-color has-text-color wp-element-button\" href=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/our-work\/certification\/leed\/\">Learn more<\/a><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group alignfull has-white-background-color has-background is-layout-constrained wp-block-group-is-layout-constrained\" style=\"margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-top:calc(var(--base-margin) * 2.5);padding-right:var(--base-margin);padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:var(--base-margin)\">    <div class=\"is-style-section-headline \">\n        <h2 class=\"has-h-4-font-size\" id=\"h-research-reports\">Research and Reports<\/h2>\n        <div class=\"wp-block-buttons\">\n            <div class=\"wp-block-button is-style-main is-style-main--small\">\n                <a class=\"wp-block-button__link has-tree-green-color\" aria-describedby=\"h-research-reports\" href=\"https:\/\/www.cagbc.org\/news-insights\/res